  id: Cervical_part_of_trapezius_muscle.L
  partName: Cervical part of trapezius muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left cervical part of the trapezius muscle Left is located along the upper
    neck and shoulder region of the canine body. Originating from the dorsal midline
    of the neck and attaching to the scapular spine, this muscle functions primarily
    to elevate and advance the scapula during forelimb movement.
  - It contributes to coordinated shoulder motion, posture maintenance, and stabilization
    of the upper thoracic region during locomotion. The cervical trapezius works
    closely with adjacent muscles to support smooth limb transitions and directional
    changes. Its activity is particularly important during walking, running, and
    climbing movements.
